Subject: [PATCH 386/987] dpaa_eth: Organize Kconfig options

[Original patch taken from QorIQ-SDK-V1.6-SOURCE-20140619-yocto.iso]

Organize all Ethernet driver options under CONFIG_FSL_DPAA_ETH
(as opposed to the current Kconfig flat structure).

Signed-off-by: Ioana Radulescu <ruxandra.radulescu@freescale.com>
Change-Id: I5285ff7fa935b933b439581fbee078a3518ea986
Reviewed-on: http://git.am.freescale.net:8181/4840
Tested-by: Review Code-CDREVIEW <CDREVIEW@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Cristian-Constantin Sovaiala <Cristian.Sovaiala@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Bucur Madalin-Cristian-B32716 <madalin.bucur@freescale.com>
Reviewed-by: Rivera Jose-B46482 <German.Rivera@freescale.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
index 92506ee..3c91e93 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpa/Kconfig
@@ -6,6 +6,8 @@ config FSL_DPAA_ETH
 	  Data Path Acceleration Architecture Ethernet driver, supporting the
 	  Freescale QorIQ chips.
 
+if FSL_DPAA_ETH
+
 config FSL_DPAA_OFFLINE_PORTS
 	bool "Offline Ports support"
 	depends on FSL_DPAA_ETH
@@ -134,3 +136,5 @@ config FSL_DPAA_ETH_DEBUG
 	default n
 	---help---
 	  This option compiles debug code for the DPAA Ethernet driver.
+
+endif # FSL_DPAA_ETH
